The audit identified a host of problems including compliance, governance, production and financial management, the statement by Congo President’s office said following a council of ministers meeting on Friday. It added that Congo’s Mines Ministry will propose measures to revamp the company. Founded in 1961, MIBA was formerly a jewel in minerals-rich Congo’s minerals industry, with gold, nickel and copper in its portfolio. However, years of mismanagement, illegal mining, smuggling, and political instability have hobbled the company. --Reuters--